The ANC is celebrating its 111 anniversary in Bloemfontein. #DStv403 BLOEMFONTEIN - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa used the party's January 8 statement to crack the whip on racism. He reiterated its vision for a non-racial society. He says South Africa is not a place to practice racism and those doing so, will feel the full might of the law. READ: Police probe alleged racism at FS resort In one of the latest incidents, three men were arrested for an alleged racial attack at a resort in Bloemfontein on Christmas day. Ramaphosa has called on young people to resist racism.  